according to grímnismál , the hall is the greatest of buildings ever made and located in þrúðvangar   in grímnismál it states : " enn hǫll hans heitir bilskírnir : í þeim sal eru fimm hundruð gólfa ok fjórir tigir " - ( five hundred floors and forty tens ) nb " hundred " in old norse actually meant 120 , as that was the basic counting system .

the mansion family : in norse mythology , this god lives in a giant mansion called bilskirnir , or " lightning "

